SIMPLE: honeydew
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Honeydew
<hw>Hon"ey*dew`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
sweet, saccharine substance, found on the leaves of trees and other
plants in small drops, like dew. Two substances have been called by this
name; one exuded from the plants, and the other secreted by certain
insects, esp. aphids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of tobacco moistened with molasses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A <er>honeydew melon</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Honeydew melon</ent>⟦br⟧
